by phansys at 2020-06-07T13:56:03Z

I think there are a lot of other good examples ([Security_through_obscurity](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Security_through_obscurity)), even from other scopes than software or IT in general ([Dark matter](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dark_matter)).
My point is, I think if we think this way we are helping or contributing a inclusive cause, we are convalidating the lack of a clear perspective (see even the last adjective) from people which is not able to distinguish between a nature concept (like "light" and "dark") and the infinite possibilities the life can adopt in a human or other beings.
I think it should not be necessary, but in order to avoid any doubt, I'm totally against in any manifestation of racism (even if that term is wrongly used).

