by javiereguiluz at 2020-06-10T12:37:03Z

@Nyholm thanks for this! As a minor suggestion, could we reconsider renaming "blocklist" as "denylist"? For some reasons:

* "Allow" and "Deny" are commonly used together (e.g. Apache Allow + Deny directives, Symfony's voters use "Deny", Symfony Controller shortcut is "denyAccessUnless...()", etc.)
* "Blocklist" looks like a typo of the more common "blacklist" ... so we may want to avoid confusion and unsolicited pull requests "fixing" this typo.
* Other open source projects that did this before also use "allow" + "deny": https://www.google.com/search?q=allowlist+denylist

